xdrawchem (2:2.1~rc0-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Restore 3D structure generation feature using OpenBabel for local
    coordinate generation (OBBuilder + MMFF94/UFF conjugate-gradients
    minimization). Replaces the defunct BUILD3D SourceForge CGI
    service that was disabled in 2.0.
  * Flatpak: cleanup bare-name desktop/metainfo/icon copies in the
    Flatpak sandbox so appstreamcli compose does not error with
    duplicate-component on the byte-identical reverse-DNS copies.
  * Repository: removed legacy Qt3 and Qt4 source trees from master
    (preserved at the v2.0 tag and earlier).
  * Repository: renamed xdrawchem-qt5/ to xdrawchem/ now that it is
    the only source tree.
  * README: updated screenshot.

 -- Bryan Herger <bherger@users.sf.net>  Sun, 26 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

xdrawchem (2:2.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Security: fix malloc/strcpy buffer overflow + use-after-free on
    QByteArray temporary (three sites in application_ob.cpp, tool_2d3d.cpp)
  * Security: replace system() with QProcess::startDetached for external
    program launch (Ghemical/KryoMol) to avoid shell injection risk
  * Security: fix fixed-buffer strcpy with user-supplied atom labels
  * Remove dead http.cpp/h module and dead XDC_SERVER environment lookup
  * Ring menu: connect Amino Acids, Nucleic Acids, Sugars, Useful Groups
    submenus so clicks dispatch to setRingAction (silent since Qt6 port)
  * Custom ring submenu: restore dispatch via per-action lambda; fix
    signal-11 crash on save (uninitialised ringmenu pointer); rebuild
    only the User-defined submenu in place to avoid paint warnings.
  * Property panel: refresh on ring placement, name-to-structure, selection
    changes, clipboard operations, undo, and delete
  * Amino Acids menu: remove non-natural amino acids that caused Qt6
    menu construction issues; users can retrieve them from PubChem instead
  * Bump Standards-Version to 4.7.2
  * Flatpak app-id renamed to io.github.bryanherger.xdrawchem
  * Flatpak: desktop and metainfo files install with reverse-DNS names
  * DEB and RPM: include the reverse-DNS file copies in the install
    manifest and %files section (CMake installs both bare and
    reverse-DNS names for system packaging compatibility)

 -- Bryan Herger <bherger@users.sf.net>  Wed, 23 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

